frameDefinitions: An Agent acts so as to cause some process to begin again after an interruption or suspension.
This frame contains transparent nouns (and some adjectives) denoting quantities of a Mass or of Individuals.
Compared to its Competitors, a Standard is at the high end of a scale with respect to some Variable.
This frame is about the static comparison of an Profiled_item to a Standard_item, often  with respect to some Attribute.

A Phenomenon is portrayed with respect to the Degree of likelihood that it will  be perceived and known, given the (usually implicit) Evidence, Perceiver, and the Circumstances in which it is considered.
In this frame a Patient is in a state of having been broken into smaller pieces.  '
frameExamples: The two countries <t>revived</t> diplomatic relations after a lull of five years.
He found them in the <t>deluge</t> of papers on his desk.
The taxpayer is supporting a system <t>unmatched</t> in wastefulness .
The Sun is putting on a show that <t>rivals</t> the most sizzling Hollywood thrillers.
It's abundantly <t>obvious</t> that we'll need to spend more time on public perception.
listRoleDefinitions: A sentient being acts with the intention of causing a process to begin again.
The process which begins again after a suspension.
The period of time during which the process is suspended.
An animate or inanimate entity, a force, or event that causes the process to resume. Volitionality is not a necessary characteristic of Causes.
The time at which the process is restarted.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> causes the <fen>Process</fen> to resume.
The <fen>Quantity</fen>-denoting <t>Target</t> word.
A substance that is being quantified.
A collection of entities.
The <fen>Standard</fen> is the entity that is located closest to the end of the scale evoked by some <fen>Variable</fen>.
The <fen>Variable</fen> is a property that evokes a scale along which the <fen>Standard</fen> is located closest to one extreme in  comparison to its <fen>Competitors</fen>.
The role <fen>Competitors</fen> denotes the entities that are exceeded by the <fen>Standard</fen> with regard to the <fen>Variable</fen>.
In active sentences, the <fen>Profiled_item</fen> is the grammatically more prominent one of the items that are compared and realized as  the subject. .
In active setnnces, the <fen>Standard_item</fen> is  the grammatically less prominent element, i.e. the object or an oblique.
This Frame Elements marks constituents that indicate in which respect Item-1 and Item-2 are equal to each other.
The <fen>Standard_attribute</fen> is used when the standard is a specific value on  a scale.
The <fen>Profiled_attribute</fen> is a particular value on a scale which is being compared to a <fen>Standard_item</fen> or <fen>Profiled_attribute</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Profiled_item</fen> rivals the <fen>Standard_item</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Profiled_item</fen> rivals the <fen>Standard_item</fen>.
The entity or facts that are undeniable given the <fen>Evidence</fen>.
The gradable aspect of a <fen>Phenomenon</fen> which concerns how likely it is that the <fen>Phenomenon</fen> be known. This frame element is incorporated by the lexical units in this frame.
A modifier expressing  the deviation of the <fen>Phenomenon</fen> from the norm or from the value for another <fen>Phenomenon</fen> in terms of how likely the <fen>Phenomenon</fen> would be known.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Phenomenon</fen> is obvious
The <fen>Patient</fen> is the entity acted on and that undergoes a change.
